## Command Line Arguments

Command line arguments will also pass into the container when run using the => https://docs.docker.com/engine/reference/builder/#cmd CMD to pass to ENTRYPOINT,

-h

```console
🚀➜ docker run -it --rm ps-perl -h
A simple perl version of ps
```

-v

```console
🚀➜ docker run -it --rm ps-perl -v
Version: 1.0
```

## Conclusions

By using the -slim variant of Debian for the base image and multi-stage builds, the resulting container size is just over 130MB. Using a smaller image like => https://hub.docker.com/_/alpine/ Alpine Linux could further reduce the image size, but could introduce => http://gliderlabs.viewdocs.io/docker-alpine/caveats/ known caveats because of => https://wiki.musl-libc.org/functional-differences-from-glibc.html musl libc and glibc differences.

```console
🚀➜ docker images
ps-perl             latest              938c3dde86d7        29 minutes ago      134MB
```

